      <paragraph>
        <num>66.</num>
        <content>
          <p>The Non-Traded Carbon Cost Effectiveness (CCE) is the estimated average social cost of abating a tonne of carbon dioxide equivalent. Whilst the CCE is a value-for money measure, it does not all wider benefits, such as air quality impacts, associated with the policy option and so should be used with caution.</p>
        </content>
