      <paragraph>
        <num>101.</num>
        <content>
          <p>Our estimate for direct costs to business reflects the Scheme Regulations 2025 as introduced and conservatively takes our maximum estimates of cost. </p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph>
        <num>102.</num>
        <content>
          <p>Actual cost to business may be lower than this maximum estimate: more ambitious heat pump cost reductions, in line with the Government’s ambition for parity of lifetime costs by 2030, the increased appeal of heat pumps to consumers as the market grows, and the impact on the market of complementary wider policy would decrease the cost significantly. Businesses may choose to pass through costs to other parts of the business and/or the prices of other products in their portfolio, although alternative approaches to funding market expansion may be available. These potential cost reductions could increase the likelihood of businesses meeting the obligation to install heat pumps instead of making a payment in lieu.  We will monitor and assess market impacts of the scheme as part of our approach to monitoring and evaluation. Table 14 below summarises the key costs to business.</p>
